content:
Absolutely! Here are some specific pieces by the contemporary cellists mentioned that you might enjoy:

1. Yo-Yo Ma: 
- Bach Cello Suite No. 1 in G Major - Prelude
- The Silk Road Ensemble - "Tabriz" 
- Yo-Yo Ma, Stuart Duncan, Edgar Meyer, Chris Thile - "Scarcely Cricket" 

2. Maya Beiser:
- "All Vows" 
- "I Will Not Remain Silent" 
- "Resistance" 

3. Zoe Keating:
- "Optimist" 
- "Exurgency" 
- "Fern" 

4. Giovanni Sollima:
- "The Lady in the Mirror" 
- "Violencelles" 
- "Lamentatio" 

5. Hildur Guðnadóttir:
- Chernobyl soundtrack - "The Door" 
- "Erupting Light" 
- "Into Warmer Air" 

I hope that gives you some great pieces to check out! Enjoy exploring these innovative and inspiring contemporary cellists.
